Program 7: Complex Login Validation 
 
 
Goal: Validate User Name (Block, small, special, number, min 8) and Password (Block, special, min 8). 
File: complex_login.html 
 
HTML 
 
 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<body> 
    <h2>Login Page Validation</h2> 
    <form id="loginForm"> 
        User Name: <input type="text" id="username"><br><small>Min 8 chars, 1 Uppercase, 1 lowercase, 1 number, 1 special char</small><br><br> 
        Password: <input type="password" id="password"><br><small>Min 8 chars, 1 Uppercase, 1 special char</small><br><br> 
        <button type="button" onclick="validateLogin()">Login</button> 
    </form>     <script>         function validateLogin() {             const user = document.getElementById("username").value;             const pass = document.getElementById("password").value; 
 
            const userPattern = /^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\d)(?=.*[\W_]).{8,}$/;             const passPattern = /^(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*[\W_]).{8,}$/; 
 
            if (!userPattern.test(user)) {                 alert("Invalid User Name format!");             } else if (!passPattern.test(pass)) {                 alert("Invalid Password format!"); 
            } else {                 alert("Login credentials are valid!"); 
            } 
        } 
    </script> 
</body> 
</html> 
 
How to run: 
1.	Save as complex_login.html. 
2.	Open in browser. Test with an invalid username (e.g., admin) and a valid one (e.g., Admin@1234). 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
